4.	How can BFS be parallelized using OpenMP? Describe the parallel BFS algorithm using OpenMP. 
BFS can be parallelized by processing multiple neighboring vertices at the same time using threads. 
Parallel BFS using OpenMP 
Different threads explore different nodes simultaneously. 
	OpenMP parallel loops are used to process neighbors. 
Algorithm 
1.	Initialize queue and visited array. 
2.	Insert source node into queue. 
3.	While queue is not empty: 
	Remove a node. o 	Process all adjacent nodes in parallel using OpenMP. 
	Mark unvisited nodes as visited. 
	Add them to queue. 
Example Code 
#pragma omp parallel for 
for(int i = 0; i < adj[node].size(); i++) {     int neighbor = adj[node][i]; 
 
    if(!visited[neighbor]) {         visited[neighbor] = 1;         #pragma omp critical         queue.push(neighbor); 
    } 
} 
Advantages 
Faster traversal 
	Better CPU utilization 
	Suitable for large graphs 
 
